snippet.title: Gin Amber Beauty REVIEW! (I finally used a Dermaroller!)
snippet.description:
Skincare Routine/Reviews @4:05 (in order listed below)

20% Vitamin C Booster - https://ginamber.com/collections/serums-creams/products/natural-vitamin-c-serum

Advanced Hyaluronic Acid Serum - https://ginamber.com/collections/serums-creams/products/advanced-hyaluronic-acid-serum

10% Vitamin C Repair Cream - https://ginamber.com/collections/serums-creams/products/repair-cream-squalane-10-vitamin-c

Natural 2.5% Retinol Serum - https://ginamber.com/collections/serums-creams/products/natural-2-5-retinol

Natural Peptide Serum - https://ginamber.com/collections/serums-creams/products/natural-peptide-serum

Cat Headband - https://ginamber.com/collections/accessories-devices/products/headband

Using a Dermaroller @10:03

Dermaroller - https://ginamber.com/collections/microneedling/products/dermaroller-0-25-absorbtion

Aqua Stamp - https://ginamber.com/collections/microneedling/products/aqua-stamp-0-25

Check out Gin Amber's channel here: https://bit.ly/2SXpOyk

#skincare #dermaroller

--------

This video is part of an (extremely long) series in which I trial a brand or theme's skincare products for two weeks; afterward, I give a review of each product based on my experience, the ingredients, and the cost. I film these bare faced (with the skincare discussed applied) for transparency. These videos are made to share my own experience and general thoughts. For YOUR routine, I always recommend visiting your dermatologist!

--------

FTC Disclosure:
Products gifted by Gin Amber Beauty. Not sponsored. All my own opinions. No affiliate links used.
